  <a href="#0" id="0">
   The original BLANC-gold [ 7 ] requires that system mentions be identical to gold mentions, which limits the metric s utility since detected system mentions often have missing key mentions or spurious mentions.
  </a>
  <a href="#1" id="1">
   The proposed BLANC is free from this assumption, and we have shown that it subsumes the original BLANC-gold.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Since BLANC works on imperfect system mentions, we have used it to score the CoNLL 2011 and 2012 coreference systems.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   The BLANC scores show strong correlation with existing metrics, especially B-cubed and CEAF-m.
  </a>
